## Crimson – E-Invoicing Platform (Frontend)

---

### What is this app?
Crimson is a **multi-country e-invoicing portal** for businesses to submit, track, and manage electronic invoices (fiscal documents) to tax authorities. Each user belongs to a client company and can operate in one or more countries (e.g. Angola, Nigeria, Greece). Documents go through a processing workflow: submitted → processed → Accepted by Agt / Rejected by Agt.

---

### Business Domain

#### Document Types
| Type              | Description                                    |
|-------------------|------------------------------------------------|
| Standard Invoice  | Primary fiscal document (~87% of volume)       |
| Credit Note       | Issued to reduce a previously billed amount    |
| Debit Note        | Issued to increase a previously billed amount  |
| Other Receipt     | Miscellaneous fiscal receipts                  |

#### Document Statuses
| Status          | Meaning                                                    |
|-----------------|------------------------------------------------------------|
| Pending         | Submitted, awaiting processing                             |
| Accepted By Agt | Processed and accepted by the fiscal authority/agent       |
| Rejected By Agt | Processed but rejected by the fiscal authority/agent       |

#### Document ID Format
`FT FT3926S2781N/151` — "FT" likely denotes a Fiscal Tax document. The trailing number is sequential per submission batch.

#### Table Fields (Recent Documents)
- **DOC ID** — Internal fiscal document identifier
- **Source Reference** — Client's own internal reference for the transaction
- **Customer** — End customer/buyer name
- **Gross Amount** — Total invoice value (displayed in K = thousands)
- **Created** — Date document was submitted to the platform
- **Status** — Current processing status (Accepted / Rejected / Pending)
- **Doc Type** — Type of fiscal document (Standard Invoice, Credit Note, etc.)

#### Multi-Country Setup
Users are assigned `allowed_countries` (e.g. `["AO", "NG", "GR"]`). The platform enforces per-country visibility — a user only sees documents for their allowed countries. Country distribution on the dashboard reflects this (e.g. Angola 95%, Nigeria 5%). Countries configured on the platform (`/api/country-settings/public`) may be a superset of a user's allowed countries.

#### User Roles & Permissions
- `role_type`: currently `["USER"]`; future roles likely include ADMIN, PARTNER, AUDITOR
- `is_partner`: boolean — partners may have elevated access across clients
- `auto_submit`: if true, documents are submitted automatically without manual confirmation
- `uploads_enabled`: controls whether the Upload button is visible/active
- `api_key`: programmatic access key for the client (`pk_...`)

